Trichet Says Spanish Banks’ Situation Improved; Must Stay Alert

-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 
2011-09-20T05:53:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/trichet-says-spanish-banks-situation-improved-must-stay-alert.html
European Central Bank President
Jean-Claude Trichet said the situation of Spanish banks has
“improved considerably,” even as “we should remain
permanently alert.” He spoke in an interview with Spanish
newspaper Expansion today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emma Ross-Thomas at 
 erossthomas@bloomberg.net  